latestPosts.caption:
Hyperpigmentation, or as some call it, skin discoloration, has been a huge part of my life for as long as I can remember. For those who don't know, it's essentially a result of excessive melanin production, which displays much more visibly in individuals with darker skin. Growing up I never really understood why I had it or how to even treat my skin to get rid of the pigments. I have it all over my body and struggled to find people who I could relate to who have the same skin problems as me. Even now, it's a recurring event for me, and I've finally accepted that it's completely normal. You're still beautiful whether you have even or uneven skin tones. If you're insecure about it as I was, I simply want to assure you that it's perfectly normal and natural to have discoloration on your skin. Often we find people on this platform showcasing perfect skin, makeup or lifestyle but I think it’s time we start normalising skin issues, body shapes as they are. Of course, while many women may choose to invest in treatment options to prevent body hyperpigmentation, it truly isn't a must. Variations of skin complexion is normal and most of all, it’s okay. The first step to overcoming your insecurities are to accept them! Periodt.
